title: Design a dynamic, sleek logo for a new grassroots political organization
name_to_incorporate: The Center for American Political Engagement
description:
The Center for American Politics Engagement is a public policy organization based in the Twin Cities of Minneapolis-St. Paul, Minnesota. Our mission is to promote thoughtful dialogue and to perform data-driven research that improves the lives of citizens in Minnesota, the Midwest, and the nation. We will lead important conversations in public forums and advocate for policy changes at the edges of conventional boundaries: elected officials, the private sector, philanthropic actors, and non-profit organizations.
Future generations deserve leadership today that strengthens democracy and equal rights, protects the environment, and promotes shared prosperity for all. We believe that government must be an instrument of good; well-crafted public policy can have a positive impact on the American people; and the role of government is a limited one that enables and empowers people to do what is right and good. Good governance, sound research and healthy analytics will promote the common good over rigid self-interest, harnessing the power of our diversity for the benefit of all.
other_notes:
***NOTE***: I am looking for a logo that can stand alone (without the org name) and especially one that doesn't have the org initials. Something that tells a story with the icon whether we include the name of the org or not.
We are looking for something that is **NOT** overtly patriotic (no American flag, eagle flying, etc.). It does not necessarily need to be red, white, and blue with stars and stripes, etc. but if there's a creative play on these elements, I'm open to them.
I prefer not using stock images.
Something organic, that cues grassroots engagement, open exchanges of ideas, but also feels American (whatever that means!).
